# Keep the build context small and, crucially, keep the host's node_modules
# out of it: the Dockerfile installs deps for the musl (alpine) target, and a
# host install (glibc) copied over them would break native modules (sharp, pg).
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/.swc
**/dist
**/coverage
**/playwright-report
**/test-results
**/.vercel
.git
.github
**/*.tsbuildinfo
**/*.log
# Never copy any env file into image layers (the Dockerfile does `COPY . .`).
# This covers .env, .env.local, .env.production, .env.staging, and the
# .env.production.remote the deploy workflow writes — keep .env.example only.
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example
**/payload*.db
**/payload*.db-*
